24/06/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A local court convicted three people charged with war crimes in Medak, Croatia, in September 1991. A fourth defendant was acquitted. Milorad Lazic and Nikola Konjevic each got three years in prison Wednesday (June 23rd). Mirko Marunic was sentenced to two years behind bars, while Perica Djakovic was released. The trial started in November. (Tanjug, Beta, Radio Free Europe - 23/06/10)
